زینو در لاس وگاس است و از این راه می تواند پول شویی کند و پول تمیز برای همه کار داشته باشد . در کازینو و سویت های مجلل آن است که فرماندارها ، سناتورها و نماینده های کنگره خریده می شوند ، و قدرت خان به جایی می رسد که می تواند قمار را در سراسر کشور قانونی کند اما داستان کتاب بیشتر مربوط به اعضای خانواده یک کلانتر پر نفوذ خاندان است ، مثله پیتر کلمانزا در پدر خوانده . او که دو فرزند دارد در حالی که دارد پسر خود (کراس ) را آماده ورود به خانواده می کند اما با دختر خود (کلادیا ) که فیلم نامه نویس در هالیوود است رابطه ای ندارد . خواننده از طریق کراس با دنیای پرزرق و برق قمار وشرط بندی در لاس وگاس آشنا شده ( فیلم کازینو به کارکردانی مارتین اسکورسیزی نمونه کاملی از این دنیاست ) و از طریق کلادیا با استودیوهای پرقدرت فیلم سازی و دنیای زیرزمینی آن ، روابط کارگردان ها با بازیگرها ، این که چگونه بازیگرها (البته نه تمامی آنها) با برقراری رابطه جنسی نقش خود را به دست می آورند ( مانند هاروی واینستین تهیه کننده پرقدرت در هالیوود ) . و چگونه هر زمان لازم شود هالیوود از مافیا کمک می گیرد و البته با سخاوت سهم خود را می پردازد .\u003cbr /\u003e جرم هایی که در این کتاب می خوانیم بیشتر از جنس آمریکایی هستند ، از خلاء هایی که در قانون وجود دارد ، از ضعفی که در سیستم قضایی آمریکا وجود دارد ، از افراد هیا�� منصفه که به راحتی خریده می شوند ، پلیس های فاسد ، شهادت های دروغین . شخصیت های داستان بیشتر ایتالیایی – آمریکایی هستند و در حال فراموش کردن قوانین اصیل سیسیل ، مانند امرتا ، برای همین خان به آنها اعتماد ندارد و سربازان خود را از سیسیل وارد می کند . البته آقای پوزو از طریق اصطلاحات ناب سیسیلی خواننده را کمی با فرهنگ سیسیل آشنا کرده است : مثلا همین که منقارم کمی خیس بشه کافیه ، یعنی سهم کمی از این کار کفایت میکنه .\u003cbr /\u003e در ادای دین کاملی به پدر خوانده ، خان کلریکوزیو هم به مانند خان کورلئونه سه پسر دارد (یکی را قبلا از دست داده است ) و یک دختر که آن هم مانند کانی در پدرخوانده اندکی خُل وزن است . فرزند او ، دانته ، نوه خان کسی ایست که خاندان را به چالش می کشد (ژن نامرغوب ) . دانته به وسیله عوامل خود کلانتر خان را در لاس وگاس می کشد و این کار خان را مجبور به دخالت می کند ، خان که تمام امید خود را به دانته برای رهبری خاندان بسته از دانته حمایت میکند . کراس هم پدر خود را از دست داده و هم حمایت خانواده را ، به گونه ای از خاندان متنفر می شود . ( مانند هنری هیل در فیلم رفقای خوب ، زمانی که از خاندان طرد می شود میداند که دیگر راه گریزی ندارد ،یا باید با خانواده بجنگد یا خود را به پلیس تسلیم کند ). کراس باید دانته را بکشد ، قبل از این که دانته او را بکشد ، کراس زودتر عمل می کند و دانته و تیمش را نابود می کند ، او که امید و آینده خانواده را نابود کرده حال باید با عواقب کار خود روبرو شود.\u003cbr /\u003e \u003cbr /\u003eدر دنیای استاد پوزو هیچ گریزی از اشتباه نیست ، هیچ شخصیتی حتی خان هم کامل نیست ، چه خان کورلئونه که با فردو ضعیف بیرون می رود و تیر می خورد ، چه خان کلریکوزیو که آینده خاندان خود را روی فرد نامناسب بنا کرده است . آقای پوزو دنیای ایده آل خان ها را به خوبی شرح می دهد : دنیایی که در آن فساد و خلاف قانونی و نهادینه شده باشد ، دنیایی که در آن مردان قانون ابزار گانگسترها باشند و برای اجرای دستورات آن ها عمل کنند. \u003cbr /\u003eدنیایی که شاید بی شباهت با دنیای فعلی ما نباشد . \u003cbr /\u003e","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/92905048?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"mario-puzo","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/92905048?shelf=mario-puzo"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2698183266"},"likeCount":58,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":9,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:614778":{"id":614778,"__typename":"User","legacyId":614778,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1194930432i/614778.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":9467,"viewableName":"Ahmad Sharabiani","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/614778-ahmad-sharabiani","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":53914},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.SqSKPtayXodWXBVy0vsevg":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.SqSKPtayXodWXBVy0vsevg","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.AkiGhGWfLdC2xcAS23X4_A"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:614778"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1638536519900,"createdAt":1466935139000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1515074537000,"text":"The Last Don, Mario Puzo\u003cbr /\u003eتاریخ نخستین خوانش: بیست و ششم ماه ژوئن سال 2009 میلادی\u003cbr /\u003eعنوان: آخرین پدرخوانده؛ نویسنده: ماریو پوزو؛ مترجم: حبیب الله شهبازی؛ تهران، افق، 1386؛ در 637 ص؛ شابک: 9643693228؛ موضوع: داستانهای نویسندگان قرن 20 م\u003cbr /\u003eداستان کوچ مافیای ایتالیا به آمریکا ست. آخرین پدر خوانده حکایتی است از آمیزش سنت و مدرنیته. انسانهای سنتی و عشیره ای میکوشند در جامعۀ مدرن آمریکایی نه تنها زنده بمانند بلکه رشد کنند و به ثروتهای کلان دست یابند. نظام قبیله ای برای سیسیلیهای مهاجر کلید جادویی پیروزی بر جامعۀ مدرن است. ا. شربیانی","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/614778?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"historical","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/614778?shelf=historical"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"novels","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/614778?shelf=novels"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"fiction","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/614778?shelf=fiction"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"mystery","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/614778?shelf=mystery"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"20th-century","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/614778?shelf=20th-century"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1679543774"},"likeCount":38,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:16842102":{"id":16842102,"__typename":"User","legacyId":16842102,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1368277474i/16842102.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":2657,"viewableName":"Mizuki","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/16842102-mizuki","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":1049},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.vYUHSjDCiLRyZe181vm7rA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.vYUHSjDCiLRyZe181vm7rA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.3emecLMMT9wM4G8lFqKckQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:16842102"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1628833049217,"createdAt":1507464163000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1601189667926,"text":"Review for the Chinese translation of this book: \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3556267439\"\u003ehttps://www.goodreads.com/review/show...\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eLet them swim to the bottom of the ocean.\u003c/i\u003e -Don Domenico Clericuzio\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e...and this badass Don who has ran a crime family for decades actually means what he said, guys.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e...and this, is my most favorite line from this book. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1515252497ra/24846619.gif\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(Link: \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://giphy.com/gifs/movie-godfather-the-3o7bujq5yoFwhPClKE\"\u003ehttps://giphy.com/gifs/movie-godfathe...\u003c/a\u003e)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eStrange that I was clueless about what Don Clericuzio actually meant when he causally commented (usually in the middle of his business meetings with his sons and trusted nephew, etc) 'let them/him/her swim to the bottom of the ocean'; the true meaning of these words had totally escaped me, but once I realized its true meaning, I was thrilled!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOkay, back to the story itself. At the beginning of the book, we see Don Clericuzio ( who is at the height of his power) made plan for his loved ones: the Family would withdraw itself (mostly) from illegal dealings, his three sons would go into different legal (but money-making) businesses; as to his trusted nephew Joseph 'Pippi' Le Dena, while the man would continue his job as the Family's number one hitman, still the Don arranged for him to move to Las Vegas to look after the Family's gamble business.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePippi was one of the few people whom the Don trusted the most, but he had done one thing which weakened his position within the Family: he had married a beautiful wife who could hardly fit into the Family, even worse, the poor woman had no idea who her husband really was.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWith the Don's blessing, Pippi's newborn son Cross, and the Don's own grandson Dante (son of the Don's widowed daughter) were christened at the very same day. The Don wished for these two infants to grow up and one day move on to the 'society', yet he could not foresee the fiery rivalry between Cross and Dante after they grew up, and the conflicts within the Family could easily disturb the future of the Clericuzio clan.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe Clericuzio clan is...you guessed it....is quite a copy of the Corleone Family from \u003ci\u003eThe Godfather\u003c/i\u003e: one badass Don as the family's leader, three sons, one widowed daughter, one adopted son/nephew, a wife who only slowly comes to realize her husband's secrets, blah blah blah. The similarities in the character's setting and the story's structure are undeniable. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHowever, in \u003ci\u003eThe Last Don\u003c/i\u003e we see a lot more about how the members of the third generation of a powerful crime family would turn up to be: we get the story of Cross and Dante, as they represent two different future for the Family.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAs a main character, Cross has better development and internal struggles than Dante--the latter is painted as a violent, unlikable jerk throughout the book. We see the 20 years old Cross entered the 'family's business' as a young adult, slowly building up his reputation through the years, facing difficult missions and setbacks, and struggling between loyalty for his father (Pippi) and/or the Family and his goodwill. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI also like how we can see how a crime family operates, how these people run their business and how they 'deal' with traitors and enemies (all written in a down-to-earth, matter-of-fact manner) through the storylines of Cross and his father.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003ePS: Pippi's story really reminds me of a Chinese slang: \u003cinput type=\"checkbox\" class=\"spoiler__control\" aria-label=\"The following text has been marked spoiler. Toggle checkbox to reveal or hide.\" onchange=\"this.labels[0].setAttribute('aria-hidden', !this.checked);\" id=\"e3ba001f-ab17-4d98-8e20-957e7ad9cdda\" /\u003e\u003clabel aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"spoiler\" for=\"e3ba001f-ab17-4d98-8e20-957e7ad9cdda\"\u003e\u003ci\u003ea hunting hound always winds up dying in the wilderness\u003c/i\u003e (獵狗終須山上喪)\u003c/label\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis time I'm glad to see in this story, women actually act as their own free agents instead of just voiceless, obedient wives, mothers and daughters like they did in The Godfather! Therefore female characters such as Claudia (Cross's younger sister) and Athena (well...the love interest) having their own storylines is quite refreshing (a lesbian director also plays a small part).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHowever! I really don't like all those plot lines and in-jokes about the showbiz in Hollywood and how people run business in the La la Land! \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1515252497ra/24846621.gif\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(Link: \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://giphy.com/gifs/movie-godfather-the-l4FGA5yLpEhfONOtW\"\u003ehttps://giphy.com/gifs/movie-godfathe...\u003c/a\u003e)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI know, Mario Puzo had been a script writer for Hollywood for years therefore he naturally knew a lot of insider's information; and he didn't shy away from making jokes about how script-writers and novelists were treated like third-class citizens in the showbiz. But! As light-hearted and delightful those Hollywood characters can be, all these lengthy Hollywood-plots still weights the whole story down!!!!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1515252497ra/24846620.gif\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e(Link: \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://giphy.com/gifs/movie-godfather-the-3o7bu5qlJXEXDK4gWk\"\u003ehttps://giphy.com/gifs/movie-godfathe...\u003c/a\u003e)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYet, the ending part really does make up for the shortcoming of this novel.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDid I mention that this book isn't quite up-there with The Godfather? I mean.........nothing beats The Godfather, anyway. XD\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI think the main reason why The Last Don fails to outperform The Godfather is that the sense of urgency in the story and my own emotional investment with the characters is both weaker this time. In The Godfather, the Corleone Family is at great risk when we meet them: Don Vito Corleone was injured and his son Mike must recuse his father and siblings, who wouldn't be touched by the loyalty and sadness he displays?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn the case of the Clericuzio Family, they are already secured in their power when we meet them and there isn't much of a crisis to be spoken of (until the ending part, that is). As to the romance(s)...let's face it, despite Mr. Puzo's mastery at crafting his world of outlaws and organized crime, he just wasn't as great when he was writing about the romantic relationships between men and women.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eReview for The Godfather: \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1363548268?book_show_action=false\u0026amp;from_review_page=1\"\u003ehttps://www.goodreads.com/review/show...\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e\u003c/[\"br\"]\u003e","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16842102?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"pretty-good","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16842102?shelf=pretty-good"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"crime-fictions","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16842102?shelf=crime-fictions"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2147027847"},"likeCount":35,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":2,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:32799998":{"id":32799998,"__typename":"User","legacyId":32799998,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1469767858i/32799998._UY200_CR32,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1068,"viewableName":"Erin ","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/32799998-erin","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":986},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.ShInn0QASx4Xe9NwlLc5MA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.ShInn0QASx4Xe9NwlLc5MA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.3emecLMMT9wM4G8lFqKckQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:32799998"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1614574632708,"createdAt":1594166592644,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1601310761261,"text":"Jar of Death Pick #37\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e4.5 Stars! \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI discovered The Last Don before I had ever even heard of The Godfather. When I was a kid I watched The Last Don on I believe CBS as a Movie of the Week(fellow old people do you remember those?) and I really liked it. I told my mom about it and she mentioned The Godfather, she said I should watch it, so we went to Blockbuster ( God! I'm old) and I rented all 3 Godfather movies. I obviously loved the first two and I no longer acknowledge Part III. I then went to Borders(I should live in a nursing home) and bought The Godfather and The Last Don in book form. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe Godfather I read and liked at the time but as I've aged I've grown to love it more and more. The Last Don novel I didn't like at all. I thought it was boring and until now I had never picked it up again. So imagine my surprise when on a second reading of this I loved this book! It is a lot slower paced than The Godfather but I could appreciate that more as an adult. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe Last Don is about.... The Mafia and Hollywood and Las Vegas. Instead of following the Corleone family this time we follow the Clericuzio family. While there were obvious parallels between the two I felt like they were two completely different families. The Last Don despite the title is less about The Don and more about the younger less criminally inclined generation. I liked the push and pull between the criminal side and the legal side. The Last Don is less violent then The Godfather but its still a brutal read. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI don't need to recommend a Mario Puzo novel because either you're into Mafia novels or you're not. But I loved it!","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/32799998?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"september-2020","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/32799998?shelf=september-2020"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3431394625"},"likeCount":32,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":6,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.xGiFD2JFLQ9RgHChDpEoCw":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.xGiFD2JFLQ9RgHChDpEoCw","__typename":"Book"},"User:43718887":{"id":43718887,"__typename":"User","legacyId":43718887,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1481063146i/43718887._UX200_CR0,77,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":152,"viewableName":"Hasham Rasool","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/43718887-hasham-rasool","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":38},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.X3MWxVn_HFOAFVyRI4w9Aw":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.X3MWxVn_HFOAFVyRI4w9Aw","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.xGiFD2JFLQ9RgHChDpEoCw"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:43718887"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1638432918725,"createdAt":1439110868000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1491068847542,"text":"It is a good book Alhamdulillah but I prefer 'The Godfather' than 'The Last Don'. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eCross De Lena does remind me of Michael Corleone.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eDomenico Clericuzo and Vito Corleone are oppositions because Domenico Clericuzo is a wise and ruthless man who is determined see his heirs established in legitimate society but whose vision is threatened when secrets from the family's past spark a vicious war between two blood cousins. Vito Corleone is a friendly man, a just man, a reasonable man, the deadliest Lord of the Cosa Nostra.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eMy favourite characters are Cross De Lena and Domenico Clericuzio.","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/43718887?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"fiction","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/43718887?shelf=fiction"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1358877658"},"likeCount":32,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:42316620":{"id":42316620,"__typename":"User","legacyId":42316620,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1642952885i/42316620._UY200_CR49,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":926,"viewableName":"Azet","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/42316620-azet","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":153},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.DCud1Vn2lSuR4DLjQE0pCQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.DCud1Vn2lSuR4DLjQE0pCQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.xGiFD2JFLQ9RgHChDpEoCw"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:42316620"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1604638569187,"createdAt":1598602667793,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1604562975670,"text":"I have now finished reading the swedish translation of Mario Puzo`s \"The Last Don\" which is another crime mystery thriller that takes you into the powerful empire of the Clericuzios.Like many other readers,i couldn`t help but compare this novel to the classic favourite \"The Godfather\".Puzo have a way of writing i have never experienced before in other novels.He writes in a way that gives me goosebumps and knows how to draw you into his world and make me care about his characters,good or evil.Domenico Clericuzio is the Don in this tale of destruction and betrayal and is obsessed with the dream of making his family business legal one day in the future for the sake of his grandchildren.But the past war against the other Mafia clan Santiados has left a terrible secret that threatens to destroy everything he holds dear.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI loved reading this novel,especially the parts with the Clericuzios who intrigued me with their Anti-hero characteristics but had great honor and loyalty towards each other.Their clans greatest assasin was Don`s nephew Joseph \"Pippi\" De Lena who was a mix in between Michael and Sonny Corleone which made him a very strong character in my eyes.His son who is actually the main-character in this novel Cross De Lena was another favourite character of mine since he represented much more humanity than the other Clericuzios since he often questioned their morals in life.I feel kinda bad for saying this,but i disliked all the female characters in this story despite their feminist view of the world and were women who had backbones in front of the Clericuzio clan.To me they were never ahead in front of the Clericuzio men,but garn damn how they sounded stupid every time they tried to outflank them.One scene for an example is when Pippi`s wife Nalene refused to share the custody of their son and daughter when they agreed to divorce.That scene made me want to slap her,especially since she did it with such great disrespect when she knew what a dangerous man Pippi actually was if he was to become your enemy.I also disliked Cross love-interest,the actress Athena.She was made for the readers to sympathize with her,but i found her so incredibly boring and stupid.For once i wished for Cross to not end up with her boring ass.Then we have Cross sister Claudia Clericuzio who becomes a script writer in Hollywood-gosh every scene with her made me cringe!Then we have the lifestyle of Hollywood and their disgusting non-morals and hypocrisy.That`s a world i want to have no part of since the famous people there can`t ever figure out how to be happy.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI do not regret reading \"The Last Don\",its a work of art and i loved following the Clericuzio clan.Don Clericuzio is a complex but very ruthless Don,who is more feared than loved.He allowed no mistakes in operations or plans but still had a forgiving streak when it came to his family.He tried to give his growing psychopath of a grandchild a chance while growing up,but that one betrayal destroyed every chances.I did not expect that Don had seen so far ahead of the consequences of that one betrayal,and my respect for him only strengthened after that.","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/42316620?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"classics","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/42316620?shelf=classics"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"drama-family-life","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/42316620?shelf=drama-family-life"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"adventure-mystery-suspense-thriller","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/42316620?shelf=adventure-mystery-suspense-thriller"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"books-made-into-movies","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/42316620?shelf=books-made-into-movies"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3491681695"},"likeCount":22,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":4,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:51625447":{"id":51625447,"__typename":"User","legacyId":51625447,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1560741685i/51625447._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":154,"viewableName":"E8RaH!M","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/51625447-e8rah-m","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":43},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.JVBiwPmfEJcJUOWfCn_pdA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.JVBiwPmfEJcJUOWfCn_pdA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.AkiGhGWfLdC2xcAS23X4_A"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:51625447"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1629493489622,"createdAt":1627117690254,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1627219384866,"text":"امتیاز 4/5 \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cb\u003eماریو پوزو بی شک باید در اولین فرصت توسط پلیس فدرال آمریکا تحت تعقیب قرار میگرفت. \u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cb\u003eپیش زمینه\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eسال های 965 تا 1072 میلادی، بیش از 100 سال جزیره سیسیل و برخی دیگر از شهرهای جنوب ایتالیا تحت سلطه و کنترل اعراب بوده است. ساختار خانواده محور و استوار بر روابط بین اعضاء گروه های مافیای سیسیلی را به جا مانده از ساختار عشیره ای اعراب میدانند. همچنین برخی از ارزشهای مافیایی مانند وفای به عهد، جوانمردی، رازداری و پرهیز از خیانت، و خانواده دوستی را به جا مانده از دوران هرچند کوتاه سلطه ی مسلمانها بر جنوب ایتالیا میدانند. حدود 100 سال پیش با فشار بی حد و حصر حکومت فاشیستی ایتالیا به گروه هایی مافیای جنوب ایتالیا، فوج فوج از افراد این گروه ها برای زنده ماندن به آمریکای جوان مهاجرت میکردند. به کشوری که درگیر کار و صنعت و ارزشهای آزادی خواهانه است. تنها چیزی که این مهاجرین را میتوانست در این کشور جدید زنده نگه دارد خانواده بود. سیسیلی ها اول از همه گرد هم جمع میشدند و گروه هایی برای کمک به هم ایجاد میکردند و آرام آرام در مقابل ارزشهای جامعه ی آمریکا از شیوه هایی مانند رشوه، تهدید، قتل و کلاهبرداری استفاده کردند تا خود را به عنوان یک قدرت تاثیر گذار مطرح کنند. \u003cbr /\u003eآنها واردات انجام میدادند، موارد میفروختند، هتل میخریدند و قمارخانه راه می انداختند تا آدمهای مشهور را به دام بیاندازند، ستاره های مورد نظرشان را در فیلمها می‌چپاندند، با رشوه به سیاست مدارها قوانین مورد نظرشان را تصویب می‌رساندند، با تطمیع عوامل پلیس از قانون فرار می‌کردند و قاضی‌های دادگاه‌ها هم برای زنده ماندن مجبور بودند احکامشان را کمی بچرخانند. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cb\u003eو اما کتاب\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eذکر اینهمه جزییات هیجان انگیز از فرهنگ و رفتار و عملکرد و جنایات مافیای سیسیل و آمریکا تنها از کسی بر می‌آید که خودش سال‌ها عضوی مورد اعتماد از مافیا بوده باشد. چنان ارتباطات در این کتاب با دقت ظرافت طرح ریزی شده که میتوان ماریو پوزو را با شکمی بر آمده میان رفت آمد نوه‌ها و بچه‌ها تصور کرد که روی یک صندلی چوبی نشسته و سیگار برگش را دود می‌کند و گاهی هم شکمش را می‌خاراند. نویسنده برخی قوانین و خرده فرهنگ‌های مافیایی را برای ما شرح می‌دهد.اصطلاحات هیجان انگیزی مثل:\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cb\u003eکامونیون\u003c/b\u003e: قتل انجام می‌شود و طوری برنامه‌ریزی می‌شود تا مخالفین یا بازماندگان متوجه شوند که قتل توسط ما انجام شده است و اینگونه پیغام ارسال می‌شود.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cb\u003eکانفرمیشن\u003c/b\u003e: قتل مخالف در شرایطی که نخواهیم پیغامی برای مخالفین یا بازمانده مخابره شود به صورتی ناشناس انجام شده یا جسد مفقود می‌شود. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cb\u003eقانون اُمرتا\u003c/b\u003e: هیچ عضوی از مافیا حق ندارد با پلیس همکاری کند حتا اگر مافیا پدر و برادرش را به قتل رسانده باشد. این اصطلاح در فرهنگ مافیای سیسیلی مترادف مردانگی و جوانمردی قرار داده شده. شبیه همان قانونی که در دوران تحصیل هنگام تعطیل کردن کلاس‌ها برخی آن را می‌شکستند که مشخصا مستوجب مرگی سخت و عبرت آموز بود.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eروایت کتاب در جزییات روابط مافیایی به نظرم از کتاب \u003ca href=\"https://goodreads.com/book/show/7400482._________\" title=\"پدرخوانده by Mario Puzo\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eپدرخوانده\u003c/a\u003e هم تکمیل‌تر است. فو‌ق‌العاده جذاب. در حین خواندن، زمان و مکان از دست می‌رود، از بس که ماجرا پشت ماجرا برایتان ردیف می‌شود. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eنکته‌ی متمایز این کتاب نسبت به سایر آثار آمریکایی، پرداخت دقیق به دنیای هالیوود است. نقش تعیین کننده روابط جنسی تهیه کننده و کارگردان و عوامل اصلی یک کمپانی فیلم‌سازی با بازیگران زیباروی زن در انتخاب بازیگر یا ستاره شدن یک نوآموز. دوز و کلکی که آن‌ها برای بیرون کشیدن حق یک بازیگر یا سرمایه‌گزار از حلقومش سوار می‌کنند. بده بستان‌های پیچیده حقوقی و نقش وکلا در این بازی.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eحالا ببینید اگر این دو طایفه‌ی بی‌رحم - گروه‌های مافیایی و دنیای فیلم‌سازی هالیوود- به هم برسند و بر سر طعمه‌ای سرشاخ شوند چه بلوایی به پا می‌شود. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eماریو پوزو اهل تحلیل‌های طولانیِ درون ذهنی نیست. هر چه هست عینی است. صحنه‌ها با طراحی عالی، موقعیت‌ها با توصیفات کامل و شخصیت‌های جا افتاده، در جای جای روایت کار گذاشته شده‌اند که حاصل یک کتاب خواندنی در آمده که وقتی می‌خوانیدش انگار فیلم سینمایی را با تمام خدم و حشمش دیده‌اید.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eغیر از برخی از اتفاقات هندی بقیه کتاب عالی و فراموش نشدنی بود.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eپینوشت: ای کاش فیلمی هم بر اساس این کتاب ساخته میشد\u003cbr /\u003eپینوشت دو: یک مینی سریال در سه قسمت گویا ساخته شده \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eخلاص","rating":5,"shelv